Task: Define timing baseline semantics\n\nSummary: Added lib/practice/timing-baseline.ts with reusable, course-agnostic types and constants for timing baselines.\n- problemFamilyId is a generic string so callers can use activityId, componentKey, or composite IDs.\n- TIMING_BASELINE_MIN_SAMPLES = 10 (conservative default).\n- Speed bands: fast (<0.5x), expected (0.5-1.5x), slow (1.5-2.5x), very_slow (>2.5x).\n- Documented why median/percentiles are preferred over mean (outlier resistance).
